Value.author: Ain
text:
In online defence of Jessica - doesn't seem like an airhead at all. Cute delivery for sure, but that doesn't signify lack of intelligence.

The "kindness for sure" bit is basically saying "that's a given. Now let's use this time to be more specific". And the cliff-diving is like saying "I'm an experienced traveller too and I'm willing to have fun with you out there". Girl in red hadn't actually left the continent - that's a major experiential disparity, especially for someone who is used to navigating cultural difference.

Value.author: -ihhssan-
text:
Watching Outlander has made me a way better english listener. Because the Scottish accent is one of the most difficult to understand for a foreigner (I'm French, it's just my opinion ;)), listening to it over and over and over again made be accustomed to the little things, tricky pronunciations and certain words that only exist in the Scottish vocabulary. 6 seasons later and I can pretty much understand everything without any help from the subtitles. It's pretty nice !
Thanks for making a video of one of my fav tv show !!
